** Location: Multiple locations – Melbourne, Adelaide, Brisbane, Newcastle, Parramatta or Perth **

** Type: 12 months Fixed Term Contract, Full Time **

##  The opportunity

An exciting opportunity has become available for a Claims System Specialist
within our Short Tail Technical Team. The successful candidate will be joining
a team who work with our operational claims teams to ensure the claims systems
support their activities, processes and customer needs. We place a strong
focus on ensuring we continuously deliver solutions by understanding the needs
of our business, our users and customers.

##

##  Your new role

  * Provide support and guidance to users across all Claims systems including integrated back end systems 
  * Create, manage and execute system testing including UAT, PVT and Regression. 
  * Manage our Enquiry Inbox by responding to a wide range of requests from the business and/or IT 
  * Review and reconcile Inbound / Outbound Document Management and Automation system issues 
  * Initiate and/or participate in workshops to gather requirements to be documented and identify an optimal solution with the Product/Business owner and our development teams 
  * Raise and manage system issues and liaise with user and IT to drive resolutions 
  * Identify and implement process improvements and assist in the development and implementation of assigned projects 

##

##  About you

We are looking for a solution focused, analytical person, who prides
themselves on providing an exceptional customer experience at every point of
contact. Self-motivated with exceptional attention to detail, you will
maintain these levels of excellence through times of change and display
resilience in the face of a challenge.

  * Strong analytical, problem solving and process mapping skills 
  * Time management and organisational skills with a solutions outcome focus 
  * Exceptional negotiation and influencing skills with an agile and critical mindset 
  * Ability to form and maintain stakeholder relationships as well as effective communication skills across a wide range of levels 
  * Ability to work autonomously, show initiative and establish priorities around competing tasks and timeframes 
  * Skills to manage and perform testing under challenging timelines and environments. 

##

##  About QBE

We can never really predict what’s around the corner, but at QBE we’re asking
the right questions to enable a more resilient future – helping those around
us build strength and embrace change to their advantage.

We’re an international insurer that’s building momentum towards realising our
vision of becoming the most consistent and innovative risk partner.

And our people will be at the centre of our success. We’re proud to work
together, and encourage each other enable resilience for our customers, our
environment, our economies and our communities.

With more than more than 13,000 people working across 27 countries, we’re big
enough to make a real impact, but small enough to provide a friendly
workplace, where people are down-to-earth, passionate and kind.

We believe this is our moment – what if it was yours too?

Your career at QBE — let’s make it happen!

